pokespecies.name: Abra
pokespecies.pokedextext: Using its ability to read minds, it will identify impending danger and TELEPORT to safety.

pokespecies.name: Alakazam
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its brain can outperform a supercomputer. Its intelligence quotient is said to be 5,000.

pokespecies.name: Kadabra
pokespecies.pokedextext: It emits special alpha waves from its body that induce headaches just by being close by.

pokespecies.name: Aerodactyl
pokespecies.pokedextext: A ferocious, prehistoric POKéMON that goes for the enemy's throat with its serrated saw-like fangs.

pokespecies.name: Articuno
pokespecies.pokedextext: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear to doomed people who are lost in icy mountains.

pokespecies.name: Bellsprout
pokespecies.pokedextext: A carnivorous POKéMON that traps and eats bugs. It uses its root feet to soak up needed moisture.

pokespecies.name: Victreebel
pokespecies.pokedextext: Said to live in huge colonies deep in jungles, although no one has ever returned from there.

pokespecies.name: Weepinbell
pokespecies.pokedextext: It spits out POISONPOWDER to immobilize the enemy and then finishes it with a spray of ACID.

pokespecies.name: Bulbasaur
pokespecies.pokedextext: A strange seed was planted on its back at birth. The plant sprouts and grows with this POKéMON.

pokespecies.name: Ivysaur
pokespecies.pokedextext: When the bulb on its back grows large, it appears to lose the ability to stand on its hind legs.

pokespecies.name: Venusaur
pokespecies.pokedextext: The plant blooms when it is absorbing solar energy. It stays on the move to seek sunlight.

pokespecies.name: Butterfree
pokespecies.pokedextext: In battle, it flaps its wings at high speed to release highly toxic dust into the air.

pokespecies.name: Caterpie
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

pokespecies.name: Metapod
pokespecies.pokedextext: This POKéMON is vulnerable to attack while its shell is soft, exposing its weak and tender body.

pokespecies.name: Chansey
pokespecies.pokedextext: A rare and elusive POKéMON that is said to bring happiness to those who manage to get it.

pokespecies.name: Charizard
pokespecies.pokedextext: Spits fire that is hot enough to melt boulders. Known to cause forest fires unintentionally.

pokespecies.name: Charmander
pokespecies.pokedextext: Obviously prefers hot places. When it rains, steam is said to spout from the tip of its tail.

pokespecies.name: Charmeleon
pokespecies.pokedextext: When it swings its burning tail, it elevates the temperature to unbearably high levels.

pokespecies.name: Clefable
pokespecies.pokedextext: A timid fairy POKéMON that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.

pokespecies.name: Clefairy
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its magical and cute appeal has many admirers. It is rare and found only in certain areas.

pokespecies.name: Cubone
pokespecies.pokedextext: Because it never removes its skull helmet, no one has ever seen this POKéMON's real face.

pokespecies.name: Marowak
pokespecies.pokedextext: The bone it holds is its key weapon. It throws the bone skillfully like a boomerang to KO targets.

pokespecies.name: Diglett
pokespecies.pokedextext: Lives about one yard underground where it feeds on plant roots. It sometimes appears above ground.

pokespecies.name: Dugtrio
pokespecies.pokedextext: A team of DIGLETT triplets. It triggers huge earthquakes by burrowing 60 miles underground.

pokespecies.name: Ditto
pokespecies.pokedextext: Capable of copying an enemy's genetic code to instantly transform itself into a duplicate of the enemy.

pokespecies.name: Dodrio
pokespecies.pokedextext: Uses its three brains to execute complex plans. While two heads sleep, one head stays awake.

pokespecies.name: Doduo
pokespecies.pokedextext: A bird that makes up for its poor flying with its fast foot speed. Leaves giant footprints.

pokespecies.name: Dragonair
pokespecies.pokedextext: A mystical POKéMON that exudes a gentle aura. Has the ability to change climate conditions.

pokespecies.name: Dragonite
pokespecies.pokedextext: An extremely rarely seen marine POKéMON. Its intelligence is said to match that of humans.

pokespecies.name: Dratini
pokespecies.pokedextext: Long considered a mythical POKéMON until recently when a small colony was found living underwater.

pokespecies.name: Drowzee
pokespecies.pokedextext: Puts enemies to sleep then eats their dreams. Occasionally gets sick from eating bad dreams.

pokespecies.name: Hypno
pokespecies.pokedextext: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of PSI moves such as HYPNOSIS and CONFUSION.

pokespecies.name: Eevee
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its genetic code is irregular. It may mutate if it is exposed to radiation from element STONEs.

pokespecies.name: Flareon
pokespecies.pokedextext: When storing thermal energy in its body, its temperature could soar to over 1600 degrees.

pokespecies.name: Jolteon
pokespecies.pokedextext: It accumulates negative ions in the atmosphere to blast out 10000-volt lightning bolts.

pokespecies.name: Vaporeon
pokespecies.pokedextext: Lives close to water. Its long tail is ridged with a fin which is often mistaken for a mermaid's.

pokespecies.name: Arbok
pokespecies.pokedextext: It is rumored that the ferocious warning markings on its belly differ from area to area.

pokespecies.name: Ekans
pokespecies.pokedextext: Moves silently and stealthily. Eats the eggs of birds, such as PIDGEY and SPEAROW, whole.

pokespecies.name: Electabuzz
pokespecies.pokedextext: Normally found near power plants, they can wander away and cause major blackouts in cities.

pokespecies.name: Exeggcute
pokespecies.pokedextext: Often mistaken for eggs. When disturbed, they quickly gather and attack in swarms.

pokespecies.name: Exeggutor
pokespecies.pokedextext: Legend has it that on rare occasions, one of its heads will drop off and continue on as an EXEGGCUTE.

pokespecies.name: Farfetch'd
pokespecies.pokedextext: The sprig of green onions it holds is its weapon. It is used much like a metal sword.

pokespecies.name: Gastly
pokespecies.pokedextext: Almost invisible, this gaseous POKéMON cloaks the target and puts it to sleep without notice.

pokespecies.name: Gengar
pokespecies.pokedextext: Under a full moon, this POKéMON likes to mimic the shadows of people and laugh at their fright.

pokespecies.name: Haunter
pokespecies.pokedextext: Because of its ability to slip through block walls, it is said to be from another dimension.

pokespecies.name: Geodude
pokespecies.pokedextext: Found in fields and mountains. Mistaking them for boulders, people often step or trip on them.

pokespecies.name: Golem
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its boulder-like body is extremely hard. It can easily withstand dynamite blasts without damage.

pokespecies.name: Graveler
pokespecies.pokedextext: Rolls down slopes to move. It rolls over any obstacle without slowing or changing its direction.

pokespecies.name: Goldeen
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its tail fin billows like an elegant ballroom dress, giving it the nickname of the Water Queen.

pokespecies.name: Seaking
pokespecies.pokedextext: In the autumn spawning season, they can be seen swimming powerfully up rivers and creeks.

pokespecies.name: Grimer
pokespecies.pokedextext: Appears in filthy areas. Thrives by sucking up polluted sludge that is pumped out of factories.

pokespecies.name: Muk
pokespecies.pokedextext: Thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

pokespecies.name: Arcanine
pokespecies.pokedextext: A POKéMON that has been admired since the past for its beauty. It runs agilely as if on wings.

pokespecies.name: Growlithe
pokespecies.pokedextext: Very protective of its territory. It will bark and bite to repel intruders from its space.

pokespecies.name: Hitmonchan
pokespecies.pokedextext: While apparently doing nothing, it fires punches in lightning fast volleys that are impossible to see.

pokespecies.name: Hitmonlee
pokespecies.pokedextext: When in a hurry, its legs lengthen progressively. It runs smoothly with extra long, loping strides.

pokespecies.name: Horsea
pokespecies.pokedextext: Known to shoot down flying bugs with precision blasts of ink from the surface of the water.

pokespecies.name: Seadra
pokespecies.pokedextext: Capable of swimming backwards by rapidly flapping its wing-like pectoral fins and stout tail.

pokespecies.name: Jigglypuff
pokespecies.pokedextext: When its huge eyes light up, it sings a mysteriously soothing melody that lulls its enemies to sleep.

pokespecies.name: Wigglytuff
pokespecies.pokedextext: The body is soft and rubbery. When angered, it will suck in air and inflate itself to an enormous size.

pokespecies.name: Jynx
pokespecies.pokedextext: It seductively wiggles its hips as it walks. It can cause people to dance in unison with it.

pokespecies.name: Kabuto
pokespecies.pokedextext: A POKéMON that was resurrected from a fossil found in what was once the ocean floor eons ago.

pokespecies.name: Kabutops
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its sleek shape is perfect for swimming. It slashes prey with its claws and drains the body fluids.

pokespecies.name: Kangaskhan
pokespecies.pokedextext: The infant rarely ventures out of its mother's protective pouch until it is 3 years old.

pokespecies.name: Koffing
pokespecies.pokedextext: Because it stores several kinds of toxic gases in its body, it is prone to exploding without warning.

pokespecies.name: Weezing
pokespecies.pokedextext: Where two kinds of poison gases meet, 2 KOFFINGs can fuse into a WEEZING over many years.

pokespecies.name: Kingler
pokespecies.pokedextext: The large pincer has 10000 hp of crushing power. However, its huge size makes it unwieldy to use.

pokespecies.name: Krabby
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its pincers are not only powerful weapons, they are used for balance when walking sideways.

pokespecies.name: Lapras
pokespecies.pokedextext: A POKéMON that has been overhunted almost to extinction. It can ferry people across the water.

pokespecies.name: Lickitung
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its tongue can be extended like a chameleon's. It leaves a tingling sensation when it licks enemies.

pokespecies.name: Machamp
pokespecies.pokedextext: Using its heavy muscles, it throws powerful punches that can send the victim clear over the horizon.

pokespecies.name: Machoke
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its muscular body is so powerful, it must wear a power save belt to be able to regulate its motions.

pokespecies.name: Machop
pokespecies.pokedextext: Loves to build its muscles. It trains in all styles of martial arts to become even stronger.

pokespecies.name: Gyarados
pokespecies.pokedextext: Rarely seen in the wild. Huge and vicious, it is capable of destroying entire cities in a rage.

pokespecies.name: Magikarp
pokespecies.pokedextext: In the distant past, it was somewhat stronger than the horribly weak descendants that exist today.

pokespecies.name: Magmar
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its body always burns with an orange glow that enables it to hide perfectly among flames.

pokespecies.name: Magnemite
pokespecies.pokedextext: Uses anti-gravity to stay suspended. Appears without warning and uses THUNDER WAVE and similar moves.

pokespecies.name: Magneton
pokespecies.pokedextext: Formed by several MAGNEMITEs linked together. They frequently appear when sunspots flare up.

pokespecies.name: Mankey
pokespecies.pokedextext: Extremely quick to anger. It could be docile one moment then thrashing away the next instant.

pokespecies.name: Primeape
pokespecies.pokedextext: Always furious and tenacious to boot. It will not abandon chasing its quarry until it is caught.

pokespecies.name: Meowth
pokespecies.pokedextext: Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.

pokespecies.name: Persian
pokespecies.pokedextext: Although its fur has many admirers, it is tough to raise as a pet because of its fickle meanness.

pokespecies.name: Mewtwo
pokespecies.pokedextext: It was created by a scientist after years of horrific gene splicing and DNA engineering experiments.

pokespecies.name: Mew
pokespecies.pokedextext: So rare that it is still said to be a mirage by many experts. Only a few people have seen it worldwide.

pokespecies.name: Mr. Mime
pokespecies.pokedextext: If interrupted while it is miming, it will slap around the offender with its broad hands.

pokespecies.name: Moltres
pokespecies.pokedextext: Known as the legendary bird of fire. Every flap of its wings creates a dazzling flash of flames.

pokespecies.name: Nidoqueen
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its hard scales provide strong protection. It uses its hefty bulk to execute powerful moves.

pokespecies.name: Nidoran♀
pokespecies.pokedextext: Although small, its venomous barbs render this POKéMON dangerous. The female has smaller horns.

pokespecies.name: Nidorina
pokespecies.pokedextext: The female's horn develops slowly. Prefers physical attacks such as clawing and biting.

pokespecies.name: Nidoking
pokespecies.pokedextext: It uses its powerful tail in battle to smash, constrict, then break the prey's bones.

pokespecies.name: Nidoran♂
pokespecies.pokedextext: Stiffens its ears to sense danger. The larger its horns, the more powerful its secreted venom.

pokespecies.name: Nidorino
pokespecies.pokedextext: An aggressive POKéMON that is quick to attack. The horn on its head secretes a powerful venom.

pokespecies.name: Gloom
pokespecies.pokedextext: The fluid that oozes from its mouth isn't drool. It is a nectar that is used to attract prey.

pokespecies.name: Oddish
pokespecies.pokedextext: During the day, it keeps its face buried in the ground. At night, it wanders around sowing its seeds.

pokespecies.name: Vileplume
pokespecies.pokedextext: The larger its petals, the more toxic pollen it contains. Its big head is heavy and hard to hold up.

pokespecies.name: Omanyte
pokespecies.pokedextext: Although long extinct, in rare cases, it can be genetically resurrected from fossils.

pokespecies.name: Omastar
pokespecies.pokedextext: A prehistoric POKéMON that died out when its heavy shell made it impossible to catch prey.

pokespecies.name: Onix
pokespecies.pokedextext: As it grows, the stone portions of its body harden to become similar to a diamond, but colored black.

pokespecies.name: Paras
pokespecies.pokedextext: Burrows to suck tree roots. The mushrooms on its back grow by drawing nutrients from the bug host.

pokespecies.name: Parasect
pokespecies.pokedextext: A host-parasite pair in which the parasite mushroom has taken over the host bug. Prefers damp places.

pokespecies.name: Pidgeot
pokespecies.pokedextext: When hunting, it skims the surface of water at high speed to pick off unwary prey such as MAGIKARP.

pokespecies.name: Pidgeotto
pokespecies.pokedextext: Very protective of its sprawling territorial area, this POKéMON will fiercely peck at any intruder.

pokespecies.name: Pidgey
pokespecies.pokedextext: A common sight in forests and woods. It flaps its wings at ground level to kick up blinding sand.

pokespecies.name: Pikachu
pokespecies.pokedextext: When several of these POKéMON gather, their electricity could build and cause lightning storms.

pokespecies.name: Raichu
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high voltage power.

pokespecies.name: Pinsir
pokespecies.pokedextext: If it fails to crush the victim in its pincers, it will swing it around and toss it hard.

pokespecies.name: Poliwag
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its newly grown legs prevent it from running. It appears to prefer swimming than trying to stand.

pokespecies.name: Poliwhirl
pokespecies.pokedextext: Capable of living in or out of water. When out of water, it sweats to keep its body slimy.

pokespecies.name: Poliwrath
pokespecies.pokedextext: An adept swimmer at both the front crawl and breast stroke. Easily overtakes the best human swimmers.

pokespecies.name: Ponyta
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its hooves are 10 times harder than diamonds. It can trample anything completely flat in little time.

pokespecies.name: Rapidash
pokespecies.pokedextext: Very competitive, this POKéMON will chase anything that moves fast in the hopes of racing it.

pokespecies.name: Porygon
pokespecies.pokedextext: A POKéMON that consists entirely of programming code. Capable of moving freely in cyberspace.

pokespecies.name: Golduck
pokespecies.pokedextext: Often seen swimming elegantly by lake shores. It is often mistaken for the Japanese monster, Kappa.

pokespecies.name: Psyduck
pokespecies.pokedextext: While lulling its enemies with its vacant look, this wily POKéMON will use psychokinetic powers.

pokespecies.name: Raticate
pokespecies.pokedextext: It uses its whiskers to maintain its balance. It apparently slows down if they are cut off.

pokespecies.name: Rattata
pokespecies.pokedextext: Bites anything when it attacks. Small and very quick, it is a common sight in many places.

pokespecies.name: Rhydon
pokespecies.pokedextext: Protected by an armor-like hide, it is capable of living in molten lava of 3,600 degrees.

pokespecies.name: Rhyhorn
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its massive bones are 1000 times harder than human bones. It can easily knock a trailer flying.

pokespecies.name: Sandshrew
pokespecies.pokedextext: Burrows deep underground in arid locations far from water. It only emerges to hunt for food.

pokespecies.name: Sandslash
pokespecies.pokedextext: Curls up into a spiny ball when threatened. It can roll while curled up to attack or escape.

pokespecies.name: Scyther
pokespecies.pokedextext: With ninja-like agility and speed, it can create the illusion that there is more than one.

pokespecies.name: Dewgong
pokespecies.pokedextext: Stores thermal energy in its body. Swims at a steady 8 knots even in intensely cold waters.

pokespecies.name: Seel
pokespecies.pokedextext: The protruding horn on its head is very hard. It is used for bashing through thick ice.

pokespecies.name: Cloyster
pokespecies.pokedextext: When attacked, it launches its horns in quick volleys. Its innards have never been seen.

pokespecies.name: Shellder
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its hard shell repels any kind of attack. It is vulnerable only when its shell is open.

pokespecies.name: Slowbro
pokespecies.pokedextext: The SHELLDER that is latched onto SLOWPOKE's tail is said to feed on the host's left over scraps.

pokespecies.name: Slowpoke
pokespecies.pokedextext: Incredibly slow and dopey. It takes 5 seconds for it to feel pain when under attack.

pokespecies.name: Snorlax
pokespecies.pokedextext: Very lazy. Just eats and sleeps. As its rotund bulk builds, it becomes steadily more slothful.

pokespecies.name: Fearow
pokespecies.pokedextext: With its huge and magnificent wings, it can keep aloft without ever having to land for rest.

pokespecies.name: Spearow
pokespecies.pokedextext: Eats bugs in grassy areas. It has to flap its short wings at high speed to stay airborne.

pokespecies.name: Blastoise
pokespecies.pokedextext: A brutal POKéMON with pressurized water jets on its shell. They are used for high speed tackles.

pokespecies.name: Squirtle
pokespecies.pokedextext: After birth, its back swells and hardens into a shell. Powerfully sprays foam from its mouth.

pokespecies.name: Wartortle
pokespecies.pokedextext: Often hides in water to stalk unwary prey. For swimming fast, it moves its ears to maintain balance.

pokespecies.name: Starmie
pokespecies.pokedextext: Its central core glows with the seven colors of the rainbow. Some people value the core as a gem.

pokespecies.name: Staryu
pokespecies.pokedextext: An enigmatic POKéMON that can effortlessly regenerate any appendage it loses in battle.

pokespecies.name: Tangela
pokespecies.pokedextext: The whole body is swathed with wide vines that are similar to seaweed. Its vines shake as it walks.

pokespecies.name: Tauros
pokespecies.pokedextext: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

pokespecies.name: Tentacool
pokespecies.pokedextext: Drifts in shallow seas. Anglers who hook them by accident are often punished by its stinging acid.

pokespecies.name: Tentacruel
pokespecies.pokedextext: The tentacles are normally kept short. On hunts, they are extended to ensnare and immobilize prey.

pokespecies.name: Venomoth
pokespecies.pokedextext: The dust-like scales covering its wings are color coded to indicate the kinds of poison it has.

pokespecies.name: Venonat
pokespecies.pokedextext: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats insects. It is attracted by light at night.

pokespecies.name: Electrode
pokespecies.pokedextext: It stores electric energy under very high pressure. It often explodes with little or no provocation.

pokespecies.name: Voltorb
pokespecies.pokedextext: Usually found in power plants. Easily mistaken for a POKé BALL, they have zapped many people.

pokespecies.name: Ninetales
pokespecies.pokedextext: Very smart and very vengeful. Grabbing one of its many tails could result in a 1000-year curse.

pokespecies.name: Vulpix
pokespecies.pokedextext: At the time of birth, it has just one tail. The tail splits from its tip as it grows older.

pokespecies.name: Beedrill
pokespecies.pokedextext: Flies at high speed and attacks using its large venomous stingers on its forelegs and tail.

pokespecies.name: Kakuna
pokespecies.pokedextext: Almost incapable of moving, this POKéMON can only harden its shell to protect itself from predators.

pokespecies.name: Weedle
pokespecies.pokedextext: Often found in forests, eating leaves. It has a sharp venomous stinger on its head.

pokespecies.name: Zapdos
pokespecies.pokedextext: A legendary bird POKéMON that is said to appear from clouds while dropping enormous lightning bolts.

pokespecies.name: Golbat
pokespecies.pokedextext: Once it strikes, it will not stop draining energy from the victim even if it gets too heavy to fly.

pokespecies.name: Zubat
pokespecies.pokedextext: Forms colonies in perpetually dark places. Uses ultrasonic waves to identify and approach targets.
